&lt;h1 class=&quot;smallTitle positionSubTitle brandColoredText&quot;&gt;DESCRIPTION&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;userDesignedContent company-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an Event Marketing Manager to partner with our Director of Events to bring Pontera&#39;s event strategy to life. This person will play a key role in planning and executing high-impact experiences while independently owning projects and collaborating closely with Marketing and Sales. We&#39;re looking for someone who is equal parts collaborator, executor, and creative problem solver. This role is a true partnership with the Directorof Events, helping bring our event strategy to life while continuously raising the bar for how Pontera shows up in the market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll support the planning and execution of our trade shows, hosted events, executive programs, and field marketing initiatives, while also owning projects independently when appropriate. You&#39;ll help transform ideas into exceptional experiences, contribute your own creative thinking, and ensure flawless execution from planning through onsite delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role for someone who thrives on both planning and execution. Whether you&#39;re developing booth concepts, coordinating vendors, managing logistics, packing materials, setting up onsite, or solving last-minute challenges, you&#39;re willing to do whatever it takes to deliver a seamless and memorable experience. At Pontera, no task is too small when it comes to creating events that leave a lasting impression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 class=&quot;smallTitle positionSubTitle brandColoredText&quot;&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re equally comfortable brainstorming a new booth experience as you are labeling shipping boxes, managing inventory, building a run of show, or troubleshooting onsite. You understand that exceptional events are built through thoughtful planning, meticulous execution, and a willingness to jump in wherever needed. You take pride in making the details invisible so attendees experience something extraordinary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
